        <h1>PhishSims Policy Documentation</h1>

        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>This document outlines the policies and guidelines related to the use of the PhishSims application. PhishSims is a platform designed for simulating and training users against phishing attacks. The policies defined here aim to ensure the secure and effective use of PhishSims while protecting sensitive information and maintaining compliance with relevant regulations.</p>

        <h2>Access and Authentication</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                User Accounts:
                <ul>
                    <li>Access to PhishSims is granted through user accounts.</li>
                    <li>Users must create a unique username and password during the registration process.</li>
                    <li>User accounts are non-transferable, and users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their credentials.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Authentication:
                <ul>
                    <li>PhishSims employs secure authentication mechanisms to verify the identity of users.</li>
                    <li>Multi-factor authentication (MFA) is strongly recommended to enhance security.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data Security and Privacy</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Data Collection:
                <ul>
                    <li>PhishSims collects and processes user data for the purpose of training and simulation.</li>
                    <li>Data collected may include user activity logs, training progress, and simulation results.</li>
                    <li>Personal identifiable information (PII) is collected only when necessary and with user consent.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Data Encryption:
                <ul>
                    <li>All data transmitted between the user's device and PhishSims servers is encrypted using industry-standard protocols (e.g., HTTPS, TLS).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Data Retention:
                <ul>
                    <li>PhishSims retains user data only for the duration required to fulfill its training and simulation purposes.</li>
                    <li>Users can request the deletion of their data in compliance with applicable data protection regulations.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Data Sharing:
                <ul>
                    <li>User data is not shared with third parties unless required by law or with explicit user consent.</li>
                    <li>Aggregate and anonymized data may be used for statistical analysis and improving PhishSims' services.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Acceptable Use Policy</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Authorized Use:
                <ul>
                    <li>Users are authorized to access PhishSims solely for training and educational purposes related to phishing awareness.</li>
                    <li>Any unauthorized use, including attempts to access restricted areas or perform malicious activities, is strictly prohibited.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Content Guidelines:
                <ul>
                    <li>Users are prohibited from uploading or sharing content that is illegal, offensive, or violates intellectual property rights.</li>
                    <li>PhishSims reserves the right to remove or restrict access to content that violates these guidelines.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Compliance:
                <ul>
                    <li>Users must comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and organizational policies while using PhishSims.</li>
                    <li>PhishSims may report any suspicious or unlawful activities to relevant authorities.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Support and Maintenance</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Technical Support:
                <ul>
                    <li>PhishSims provides technical support to users for resolving issues related to access, functionality, or security.</li>
                    <li>Users can contact support through designated channels for assistance.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Maintenance and Updates:
                <ul>
                    <li>PhishSims conducts regular maintenance and updates to ensure optimal performance, security, and compliance.</li>
                    <li>Users are notified in advance of any scheduled maintenance that may impact access to the platform.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

